                            <comment id="13155748" author="vivekp" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2011 08:26:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think that this issue is introduced as part of new parser changes in Pig 0.9. &lt;br/&gt;
As per my analysis, the Scalar ref used,&quot;Z1.count&quot; introduces another additional LOStore with a tmp location.&lt;br/&gt;
While processing for STORE D, it considers this extra LOStore also and thinks that it has processed all store statements.&lt;br/&gt;
Hence,the store operator for the alias &apos;D&apos; is skipped (this is happening at PigServer.Graph.skipStores() ).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The above script, could be used to replicate the scenario without multiquery, if we use PigServer to register and execute the queries.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13158265" author="daijy" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 07:35:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We use processedStores to track how many stores we&apos;ve already processed. However, we counting different things. When we count how many stores we processed, we use the plan after postProcess. When we skip stores in the logical plan, we use the plan before postProcess. The difference is the former count the scalar LOStore added by postProcess, the later not. We should make the count on the same plan.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13158655" author="daijy" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 19:17:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attach a draft patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13159767" author="olgan" created="Wed, 30 Nov 2011 02:58:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Daniel,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When do you think this can be checked in? We would like this on 0.9 branch in addition to 10 and trunk, thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
